Chief Secretaryâs Office

Melbourne 5th March 1874

Sir,

In view of the preparation of the Estimates for the year 1874.5 I have the honor to request that you will be so good as to furnish by the 15th instant a statement of the probable requirements of your Department during that period together with an estimate of the revenue (if any) expected to be received.

I have the honor to be

Sir

Your most obedient servant

Thos. Webb Ware

Acting Under Secy.
